data.title: Staff
data.meta_description: We have years of experience caring for families, from all walks of life. Each family comes to us because they know we are leaders in our profession, dedicated to excellence in service, and have the highest integrity.
data.text:
S. Keith Parsell, Owner and CEO

Keith is a native Sussex Countian, having been raised in Dagsboro with maternal roots going back to the Stockley and Blades communities. The majority of his early years were in Smyrna, DE. He is a 1974 graduate of Smyrna High School; 1976 graduate of Wesley College in Dover, and a 1977 graduate of the Cincinnati College of Mortuary Science where he was a member of the Alpha chapter of Pi Sigma Eta. He holds a Funeral Directors License in both the states of Delaware and Pennsylvania and a Morticians License in the State of Maryland. He also holds a Limited License insurance license in the State of Delaware for preneed funeral arrangements.

Keith resides in Lewes with his wife Alison and has three children: Christina, Johnathan and Andrew; four granddaughters, one grandson and two step children, Amanda and Steven. He is a member of Bethel United Methodist Church in Lewes where he sings in the choir and serves as substitute organist; is a life member of the Citizens Hose Company, Smyrna, Delaware and a member of the Citizens Hose Company Fireman's Band where he plays the trumpet.

He is an honorary member and Past Treasurer and President of the Lewes Volunteer Fire Department; member and Past Treasurer and President of the Delaware State Funeral Director's Association; former member of the Delmarva Funeral Service Assn.; member of the National Funeral Director's Assn. where he had served on the Budget Committee for two years; member of the Cremation Society of North America; former member of the Board of Directors of Delaware Hospice for over twenty years; member of the Georgetown and Bridgeville Historical Societies; and former member and treasurer of Rehoboth Beach Kiwanis Club, served as a Beebe Ambassador and is currently a member of the the Beebe Medical Foundation Board, where he serves on the finance committee. Most recently he concluded a two term-six year appointment by Delaware Governor Jack Markell on the Board of Funeral Services for the State of Delaware where he had served three years as President of the Board.

He enjoys spending time with his family, traveling, hunting and a game of golf here and there.

Alison Parsell, Chief Operating Officer

Alison, Keith's wife, joined the staff in 2003. She is a native Delawarean, raised in Dover; graduated from Caesar Rodney School District and the Peninsula General Hospital School of Radiologic Technology. She relocated to Lewes in 1980.

Alison holds an insurance license in the State of Delaware for preneed funeral arrangements.

Alison has two children: Stephen Jones and Amanda Boyer; is a member of Bethel United Methodist Church in Lewes where she is a past member of the choir, music librarian, Administrative Board Secretary, and as a Sunday School Assistant. She currently services as a lector and on the Board of Trustees of the church.

She is a former member of the Board of Director's and former assistant treasurer of the Lewes Historical Society and curator of the Doctor's Office Museum. Also, she is a former member of the Sussex County Medical Society Auxiliary where she assisted in the production of many fund raising local fashion shows.

Andrew T. Parsell, Licensed Delaware Funeral Director, Vice President

Andrew T. Parsell is the son of the owner, Keith Parsell. He is a graduate of Cape Henlopen High School and the Pittsburgh Institute of Mortuary Science. In 2010 he became a Delaware Licensed Funeral Director, after completing his resident internship with the firm. He now serves as a director on staff and is Vice President for the funeral home. He is a member of St. Jude The Apostle Catholic Church in Lewes; former member of the Lewes Volunteer Fire Department, Inc; served as President of the Delaware Funeral Directors Association for the 2015-2016 term. Like his father, he is currently in his first term of appointment to the Delaware State Board of Funeral Services by Governor John Carney. In his free time he excels as an avid golfer, fisherman and hunter.

Johnathan Parsell, Chief Financial Officer

Johnathan grew up in the family business, learning many aspects of the funeral industry. He currently oversees the financial operations of the company and assists with general management.

His previous experience includes working in financial services as a Registered Representative for some of the largest and most well-known mutual fund and financial advising companies.

He holds Bachelor of Science degrees in Marketing and Operations Management from the University of Delaware and a Master of Business Administration in Entrepreneurship and Innovation from Drexel University.

Johnathan has served as a Director on the Cadbury Foundation Board of Directors and is a former member of the Lewes Volunteer Fire Department. In his spare time, Johnathan enjoys time with his wife and daughters as well as exploring new cities and cuisines with his wife and spending time outside with his Australian Labradoodle, Cannoli.

David T. Bradley, Licensed Delaware & Pennsylvania Funeral Director

David is a licensed funeral director who joined our firm in July 2014 and is licensed to practice in the states of Delaware and Pennsylvania. He also holds an insurance license in the State of Delaware for Pre-Need Funeral Arrangements. Originally from Western New York, David proudly served in the U.S. Navy. He is a graduate of Central Pennsylvania Business School where he also served as the Director of Enrollment. David then graduated from Northampton Community College with an Associate Degree in Applied Science in Funeral Service Education and worked as a licensed Funeral Director in Lebanon, PA.

He and his wife, Carolyn, are the parents of Megan, Ben and Hope Bradley. He enjoys surf fishing and kayaking in the ocean and bays as well as volunteering with Operation SEAs the Day, Warrior Family Beach Week in Bethany Beach.

Laura E. Murabito, Licensed Delaware Funeral Director

Laura Murabito joined the company in April 2015. She was born and raised in Lewes and currently resides here with her son, Ripley. She graduated from St. Thomas More Academy in 2008.

She received her Associates Degree in Applied Science in Funeral Services at Des Moines Area Community College in 2019. After serving her internship she became a licensed funeral director in 2020. Laura is driven by her passion to care for families in the community, many of whom are life long acquaintances.

In her spare time, she enjoys baking, going to the beach, watching her beloved Philadelphia sports teams, especially the Phillies and the Eagles, and spending time with Ripley.

Michael R. Frock, Aftercare Coordinator

Mike is a Pennsylvania and Delaware licensed Funeral Director and joined the firm in 2022.

He is a graduate of York College of Pennsylvania with a bachelor’s degree in Police Administration. This education served him well as an Investigator in the US Air Force. Mike is a graduate of the Community College of Baltimore County Mortuary Science program. He is recognized as a Certified Professional in Funeral Planning from Funeral Directors Life Insurance Company, and Dr. Alan Wolfelt’s Center for Loss & Life Transitions, Fort Collins, CO. He also holds an insurance license in the State of Delaware for Pre-Need Funeral Arrangements. In his 20 plus years as a funeral director, he has advised thousands of families in creating meaningful and healing funerals.

Mike and his wife, Holly, live in Millsboro, DE with their two “Scottish Terrorists.” Mike enjoys time at the beach and on the golf course, where he says, “A good day is finding more balls than I lose.”

Scott Burdette, NFDA Certified Pre-planning Counselor & Delaware Licensed Life Insurance Producer

Scott Burdette joined the firm in April 2011. He is a Delaware Licensed Insurance Agent and has also been certified by the National Funeral Directors Association as a Pre-planning Consultant.

Scott was born and raised in Maryland and moved to Rehoboth Beach in 2002. For 33 years he worked in the food industry holding various positions as Clerks and Department Managers with Giant Food to being a Sales Representative, Retail Sales Manager, Accountant Manager and Business Manager with Acosta Sales & Marketing.

In his spare time, he enjoys spending time with his spouse, friends and family. He also enjoys time with his rescue dog Casper, working around his home and spending time on the beach.

Andrea Campanelli, Funeral Hostess

Andrea joined our firm in January 2023 as a Funeral Hostess. Raised outside DC, She joined us with a background as a hospitality industry professional with over 20 years of experience working in South Florida. In 2009, she relocated to Rehoboth Beach full-time. She spent 13 years working at 1776 Steakhouse where she was locally embraced by our friendly community.

Andrea is passionate about our country and those who choose to step up to serve. When not working, she takes pleasure in everything having to do with “Salt Life”, fun get-togethers with close friends and family, live music, biking, taking spontaneous road trips, and seeking out new culinary experiences. Her Dachshund Yorkie Mix, Zuzu, is known to accompany her on adventures.
